FBIS3-20003 "drweu058_q_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 TURKEY Government Continues Security Operations Kill 11 `Terrorists' in Hizan TA2503115394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1030 GMT 25 Mar 94 TA2503115394 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Bitlis, Mar25 (A.A.) -- Eleven separatist terrorists have been killed in two-day clashes with security forces near Hizan township in the southeastern province of Bitlis, officials said on Friday [25 March]. They told the Anatolian Agency that Thursday's death toll of four rose to 11 on Friday in continuing clashes. Two privates were also wounded. Helicopters are taking part in the security forces' operation. Over 11,000 people, including terrorists, members of security forces and civilians, have been killed in southeastern Turkey since 1984 when the separatists launched their bloody campaign for an independent state in the region.
